Initialize Primary Window (QMainWindow)

Description: Established the top-level application container. 
Unlike a basic QWidget, QMainWindow provides a dedicated space for a central widget, toolbars, and status bars, serving as the "shell" for the entire program.

Implement Screen Navigation (QStackedWidget)

Description: Initialized a QStackedWidget (named balicek_obrazovek) as the central hub. 
This acts like a deck of cards, allowing the application to switch between different "screens" (like a Menu and a Game board) without opening new windows.

Dynamic UI Generation (Menu Loop)

Description: Automated the creation of player-selection buttons using a Python list [2, 4, 6].
This keeps the code "DRY" (Don't Repeat Yourself) and makes it easy to add more player options (like 3 or 5) in the future just by changing the list.

Closure Fix in Event Handling (lambda p=pocet)

Description: Implemented a specific Python fix for loops. 
By using p=pocet inside the lambda, you ensure that each button "remembers" its own specific number. Without this,
every button would mistakenly use the last value of the loop (6).

Centralized Navigation Logic (spust_hru)

Description: Created a bridge function that receives data from the menu and prepares the next stage of the application.
This is where the game state (number of players) is passed from the "Settings" phase to the "Gameplay" phase.

Content Alignment & Labeling (QLabel)

Description: Used a QLabel for the title text.
Applied specific CSS margins and font weights to ensure the user immediately understands the purpose of the screen upon launching the app.
